{
  schema: "patter/strings@0",
  scene: "scn_tavern",
  locale: "en",
  default: true,
  strings: {
    T_scene: "The tavern is dim, thick with pipe-smoke and the smell of <bi>spilled ale</bi>.",
    T_room: "A low fire spits in the corner, throwing long shadows across the floorboards.",
    T_patrons: "A handful of patrons nurse their drinks and pretend not to watch you.",
    L_greet: "What'll it be, stranger?",
    L_greet2: "We don't get many <i>new</i> faces down this way.",
    C_work: "Ask about work",
    C_intim: "Threaten him for coin",
    C_secret: "Mention the cellar",
    C_leave: "Leave",
    T_work_lead: "You ask whether there's honest work to be had.",
    T_intim_lead: "You lean in, letting a hand rest on the hilt of your blade.",
    L_intim_warn: "Easy, now. No need for that in my house.",
    L_secret_lead: "Aye? And what would you know about the cellar?",
    L_work: "Aye - rats in the cellar. <b>Big</b> ones. Two gold if you clear them out.",
    L_work2: "Mind the far wall. Some of those stones aren't as solid as they look.",
    T_work_done: "He slides a rusted iron key across the bar.",
    L_intim: "...fine, fine. Take five gold, just keep your blade sheathed.",
    L_intim2: "And we'll forget this little misunderstanding ever happened.",
    T_lean: "You lean across the bar and murmur about the cellar.",
    L_secret: "...so you DO know. Good. We'll talk when it's quiet.",
    L_secret2: "Down the stairs, mind the third step. She's waiting.",
    T_cellar1: "The cellar stairs are slick with damp; the air tastes of cold stone.",
    T_cellar2: "Barrels crowd the dark, and something shifts behind the farthest one.",
    L_anna1: "You took your time getting down here.",
    L_bo_reply: "Quiet, Anna. Did anyone follow him?",
    L_anna2: "Sit. There's more to this than rats - and not much time to explain it.",
  },
}
